<task id="task-5613" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Use basic authentication in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">To use basic authentication in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>, do as follows:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> tab of a web service request, set the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Type</uicontrol> as <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Basic</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image href="ks-840-basic-authentication.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">basic authentication</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Pass in your username and password to authenticate the request, then click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Update to HTTP Header</uicontrol>. </cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result "><p class="- topic/p ">The username and password are encoded to the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Authorization</uicontrol> request of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">HTTP Header</uicontrol> tab, as you can see below. </p><p class="- topic/p "><image href="ks-840-basic-authorization.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">basic authorization</alt></image></p></result></taskbody></task>